                "href": "/profile/Gopika-Sajikumar"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes, BTS uses playback music at almost all of their concerts with them singing live on top of this playback whenever they can. This is done because their choreography is extremely difficult and exhausting. Rap portions are mostly excluded from playback because there are more chances of having difference in paces when doing live on top of playback for rap parts. Even dancers who are trained for more than a decade start panting and getting tired after dancing for ten minutes straight. But BTS concerts range from 30 mins- 3 hrs! Imagine having to sing (expected to be flawless) too along with all that dancing! It is totally impossible to sing 100% in such cases and hence the need for playback music. ",
