            "answer_text": "Of course they did lip sync at certain times. They have intense choreagraphies and most of the time, they need to hit some high notes that even I, as a girl with a big register, are already something. For a better performance, it is sometimes necessary to lip sync. Fans have expectations and the idols need to meed up to them. of course, this doesn\u2019t apply only to BTS, every singer out there doing shows lip syncs at least once. The voice is unpredictable and you can never know when it will super good or when it\u2019s a bad day. Lip sync helps the singers deliver an amazing performance for their fans. Edit: Wow, my english was terrible in that answer, wtf. It\u2019s like I lost a couple brain cells while writing it. I\u2019m very sorry to anyone who read this shit. I hope you understood my point anyway. ",
