            "author_info": {
                "name": "Cherie Richards",
                "href": "/profile/Cherie-Richards-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "The difference between the live singing and the recorded track can be quite dramatic - the guys tend to \u201cshout-sing\u201d during the concert (I.e. more on the beat, less flourish, more rap styled), likely to be able to maintain the cadence of the song without losing breath entirely. When they lose their breath and the voice track takes over, the difference is extremely noticeable (sounds produced rather than live). There are exceptions to the overlay of voice tracks (usually when one of the guys, typically Suga, wants to makes the audience sing a line). A specific example: in the live version of Airplane pt2 they show excellent control during verses and rap elements with no discernible (at least audible) voice track. The voice track does seem to be present / more obvious in the last 1 min, where V and JK are moderately out of breath, and the chorus voices seem more produced (less fluctuating tone given JK/Jimin/Jin/V still dancing during that part). ",
